<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-451-445  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 451 445.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  Sept 1990 v7 n9 p49(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Companies, VARs can do a better job. (of designing and equippingsystems; Collisions) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Fund, Glenn.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Large corporations make significant equipment purchases throughoutthe year and have a large installed base supporting multipleenvironments.andP;  For these reasons and because of ongoing efforts tointegrate systems, an in-house systems integration departmentmakes more sense than dealing with retail computer chains.andO;In-house staff have a clearer grasp of the precise needs of their'clients'.andP;  They are experienced in the concept of enterprise-widecomputing.andP;  While specialized value-added resellers (VARs) canoffer many of the same services as the in-house staff, this comesat additional cost.andP;  Also, large corporations can obtain volumepurchase discounts that are equal to or greater than thoseavailable through retailers.andP;  A collateral benefit to therelationship established between large corporations andmanufacturers is beta testing that aids in the development of newor enhanced products.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     AnalysisCritiqueSystem DesignPurchases.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>